A vintage-style illustration of an intricate mechanical printing press merged with flowing streams of structured data, rendered in warm sepia and amber tones. Cascading ribbons of XML-like angular brackets and nested hierarchical patterns flow from a brass clockwork mechanism into perfectly formatted document pages emerging from the other side. The scene has the aesthetic of a Victorian-era technical diagram with cross-hatched shading and ornate decorative borders. Gears, cogs, and copper pipes connect different transformation chambers where raw data visibly morphs through stages - entering chaotic and formless, passing through elaborate filter mechanisms, and exiting as crisp, organized pages. Steam wisps rise from the machinery, giving it an alchemical quality of turning base materials into refined output.
